=Episode 15=

14
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,910
Oh, no.

15
00:01:53,910 --> 00:01:54,940
Something's wrong.

16
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:56,690
Mrs. Zhao.

17
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,800
Mrs. Zhao, what's wrong?

18
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:00,970
There's a fierce battle today.

19
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:02,100
When the patrol squad

20
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:03,780
returned from scouting the enemy,

21
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:05,780
they were ambushed by Tribe One.

22
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:07,190
After getting the news,

23
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:08,570
the Lord led a team to rescue them,

24
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,660
but several men were still injured or killed.

25
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,100
The patrol squad?

26
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:18,940
Did anything happen to Wen?

27
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,970
Mrs. Zhao.

28
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:21,460
Please come out.

29
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:23,800
Coming.

30
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:28,660
I'm Lord Huaiyang's

31
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,010
patrol guard.

32
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:38,180
We are a confidential unit

33
00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:41,290
responsible for intelligence gathering.

34
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,700
Are you hurt?

35
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,850
Where are you injured?

36
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:44,110
I'm fine.

37
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:47,460
Everything will be okay.

38
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,170
I'll make sure to bring you home safely.

39
00:04:57,350 --> 00:04:59,100
A royal decree has arrived!

40
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,140
A royal decree has arrived!

41
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:08,930
Cui Xingzhou.

42
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,660
Urgent message from afar.

43
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,020
What's the court's decree?

44
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:16,730
They ordered me not to fear

45
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:17,990
and to attack

46
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:19,340
within ten days.

47
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,340
Isn't this forcing you to die?

48
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,280
Defending

49
00:05:25,470 --> 00:05:26,490
is possible,

50
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,970
but to fight now would

51
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:29,660
mean almost certain defeat.

52
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,730
I know we can't gamble the entire Zhenzhou

53
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:36,260
on a slim chance of victory.

54
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,140
But we can't keep stalling either.

55
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:43,520
But if they didn't attack,

56
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,140
you have no opportunity to exploit.

57
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:53,100
(Relatives' Village, Xizhou,
Feitang Valley, Jinjia Pass)

58
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:55,260
(Western Tribes)

59
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,850
There's a battle opportunity.

60
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:03,050
What opportunity?

61
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,520
You.

62
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:05,960
Me?

63
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:07,140
The grain just arrived.

64
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:09,460
If I strike immediately,

65
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:11,020
what would A Gushan think?

66
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,140
He would naturally think

67
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,530
that you couldn't hold back.

68
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,820
Our army is well-stocked,

69
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:20,930
strong and well-equipped.

70
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,590
Since he's good at using troops,

71
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:24,730
if I use the provisions as bait

72
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:26,850
and find a narrow and enclosed terrain

73
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,760
to launch a proactive flanking attack,

74
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,600
the chance of victory

75
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,850
could increase by at least

76
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,400
thirty percent,

77
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,530
To a tie.

78
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,960
Barbarian.

79
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:54,020
Come here.

80
00:06:55,910 --> 00:06:57,230
What did you do to my goats?

81
00:06:57,230 --> 00:06:58,460
What did you do to them?

82
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:00,260
They were fine.

83
00:07:00,470 --> 00:07:01,530
Why are they like this?

84
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,200
They can't even stand up.

85
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,680
For these few thin-legged goats,

86
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,170
I could kick them to death.

87
00:07:06,790 --> 00:07:08,460
I don't have time to poison them.

88
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:10,370
My goats had always been fine

89
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:11,970
until you came.

90
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:13,900
If it's not you, then who?

91
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,150
Let go of me.

92
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:16,830
You owe me for the goats.

93
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:17,930
She didn't poison them.

94
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,340
Look at what's in the bucket.

95
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,580
It's just some grassroots.

96
00:07:27,910 --> 00:07:29,260
It fell in when I fetched water.

97
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:34,970
This is ghost root.

98
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,270
I heard from the locals

99
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,580
when I was collecting medicine.

100
00:07:38,590 --> 00:07:39,440
Ghost root

101
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,320
grows in dark and damp places.

102
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,370
Its roots are medicinal.

103
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,440
It can cause numbness, weakness, and fatigue

104
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,340
after soaking in water.

105
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:48,120
The goats might eat hay

106
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,320
soaked in ghost root water,

107
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,970
which caused it to become like this.

108
00:08:11,910 --> 00:08:12,750
That's it.

109
00:08:14,230 --> 00:08:15,170
Finally found it.

110
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,610
Same with the ones in the bucket.

111
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:33,700
Nanny Li, this is ghost root.

112
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,870
Go over there and see

113
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:36,850
if there's more.

114
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:38,880
I'll check now.

115
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:24,950
Honey.

116
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,770
How are you feeling now?

117
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:32,070
It's alright.

118
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,540
When you were unconscious,

119
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,610
you occasionally cried out in pain.

120
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:38,490
Is there any discomfort?

121
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,300
I had a very frightening dream.

122
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,100
I dreamed of being taken
into the deep mountains.

123
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,220
I struggled desperately

124
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:56,460
but my tendons were still cut,

125
00:10:57,110 --> 00:10:58,540
and I was thrown off a waterfall.

126
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,060
What else did you dream about?

127
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:10,760
The villain

128
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:12,420
had his face covered,

129
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,220
so I couldn't see his face.

130
00:11:26,630 --> 00:11:27,580
Forget it.

131
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:30,420
In the coming days,

132
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:34,300
let's focus on getting better.

133
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:37,610
Drink your medicine first.

134
00:11:41,110 --> 00:11:41,950
Miss.

135
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:43,200
The pork knuckle

136
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,460
is a specialty of my restaurant,

137
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:46,770
but it's a bit unsightly to eat.

138
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:50,040
Cockles are more suitable for ladies.

139
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:51,730
Would you like to try it?

140
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,650
Cockles are indeed elegant.

141
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,300
I'll have the pork knuckle.

142
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,160
Alright.

143
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,590
Miss.

144
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,940
Let's first go buy some jewelry.

145
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:05,370
If the madam finds out...

146
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,650
It's just a meal.

147
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,100
No need to feel guilty.

148
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:14,890
Miss Shi.

149
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,460
Mr. Ziyu.

150
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:25,850
Miss Shi and I seem to be fated.

151
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:27,580
Miss Shi.

152
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:28,850
Are you out alone?

153
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,320
My mother allowed me to look at some jewelry.

154
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,510
Hearing this place is good,

155
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:35,820
I came in to have a seat.

156
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:40,100
The cockles here are indeed excellent.

157
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:43,490
Which table ordered the pork knuckle?

158
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:55,060
Sir, was it you?

159
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,120
No, no.

160
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,400
I'm having some light tea and meals.

161
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,850
I won't keep you any longer.

162
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,490
Where are you sending it?

163
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,340
It was this lady who ordered it.

164
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,320
This lady is clearly

165
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,250
a foodie who appreciates fine food.

166
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,960
She didn't even look

167
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,180
at other dishes

168
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,700
and only had eyes for the pork knuckle.

169
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:22,650
Please enjoy.

170
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,180
I've heard

171
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,630
that the pork knuckle here

172
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:30,370
is seared over a flame to lock in the flavor

173
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,370
and soaked in boiling water.

174
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:34,800
After being cooked, it's left
to rest for a day and night

175
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,130
before being served.

176
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,200
The meat must be tender on the inside

177
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,390
and crispy on the outside.

178
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,650
- You all go out.
- Alright.

179
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,120
Yes.

180
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,540
You're a foodie,

181
00:13:46,110 --> 00:13:47,340
but you're not so lucky.

182
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,940
But don't worry.

183
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,160
With me here,

184
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:54,130
even if General Shi were here,

185
00:13:54,510 --> 00:13:55,540
he wouldn't say anything.

186
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,220
Miss Shi,

187
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,130
please feel free to eat.

188
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,970
Enjoy.

189
00:14:37,470 --> 00:14:38,890
Mr. Ziyu.

190
00:14:44,350 --> 00:14:45,700
I used to eat meat

191
00:14:46,110 --> 00:14:47,160
and drink wine heartily

192
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,100
at Mount Yang.

193
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,610
I might've startled you.

194
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,040
Is it delicious?

195
00:15:06,110 --> 00:15:07,540
Thank you for accommodating me

196
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,220
as a rude man.

197
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,730
You are quite considerate.

198
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:16,920
I heard from my father

199
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,350
that you've read many books

200
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:20,060
and are skilled at Go.

201
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,850
My birth mother passed away early.

202
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,940
No one ever taught me the Eight Arts.

203
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:26,630
I wonder

204
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:28,610
if you would be willing to teach me Go.

205
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:33,010
On the Go board, these nine points

206
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,180
are called stars.

207
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,400
The center point is called

208
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,710
the Tianyuan.

209
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:40,340
I'll start by occupying the Tianyuan.

210
00:15:42,830 --> 00:15:44,060
As a beginner, you should

211
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,460
start by occupying the corners, then the sides,

212
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:48,250
so as not to be caught off guard.

213
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:50,200
If you start with Tianyuan,

214
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,250
you'll have a weak start,

215
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,820
vulnerable to later control.

216
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,320
It's like giving

217
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,940
the first move to your opponent.

218
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:59,420
The moves represent the player.

219
00:15:59,780 --> 00:16:01,010
The person teaching you Go

220
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,870
is showing you

221
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:04,700
their temperament completely.

222
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,340
Please cherish it.

223
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:16,490
If I win your game,

224
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,400
doesn't that mean

225
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,460
I surpass you in character?

226
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:23,710
Sorry.

227
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:26,730
I only know how to play Go,

228
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:28,650
not to teach it.

229
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,180
Sorry for asking this.

230
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,060
Come on. Careful.

231
00:16:44,470 --> 00:16:45,310
Honey.

232
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,060
Why are you out of bed?

233
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:49,440
I've been lying down enough.

234
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,420
I wanted to come out and stretch my legs.

235
00:16:53,350 --> 00:16:55,540
What delicious food did you bring me?

236
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,820
Wild fruits from the mountains.

237
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,280
It's chilly here.

238
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,100
Nanny Li, warm them up.

239
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:02,770
- Yes.
- Please sit down.

240
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:05,210
There's military duty,

241
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,370
so I can't stay for too long.

242
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:10,400
You've been commuting because of me.

243
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,210
At least sit, have some hot tea,

244
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,580
and rest for a while.

245
00:17:16,030 --> 00:17:16,870
Honey,

246
00:17:16,990 --> 00:17:18,820
the medicine shop has been lively these days.

247
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,030
First, Ms. Lin came,

248
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:22,470
then Mrs. Wang.

249
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:23,310
Do you know?

250
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:25,020
Mrs. Wang's goat

251
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,070
suddenly collapsed

252
00:17:26,070 --> 00:17:27,020
and couldn't get up.

253
00:17:27,470 --> 00:17:29,130
When I went to check, I found

254
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,210
ghost roots soaked in her bucket.

255
00:17:31,470 --> 00:17:32,780
Ghost roots? And then?

256
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,920
Ghost root is a local term

257
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,210
not commonly seen elsewhere.

258
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,840
Though ghost root

259
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:38,780
looks unremarkable,

260
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:43,060
if it's soaked in hay feed,

261
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,340
its effect is very strong.

262
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:47,210
It's a pity for those few goats.

263
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,510
They probably

264
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:49,690
haven't recovered yet.

265
00:17:57,230 --> 00:17:58,070
Honey.

266
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:00,980
If ghost roots

267
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,780
can make goats collapse,

268
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,260
what about war horses?

269
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:09,580
What do you mean, dear?

270
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,890
The western tribes use cavalry.

271
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:13,650
What I mean is

272
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:14,960
if there's a way

273
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,820
to make their war horses eat feed

274
00:18:16,990 --> 00:18:18,070
soaked with the medicine,

275
00:18:18,070 --> 00:18:18,930
they'd become weak,

276
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,130
which would greatly reduce their combat power.

277
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,610
That's a good idea.

278
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:28,890
But how do we deliver

279
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,340
the feed?

280
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,440
We can collect

281
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:35,210
ghost root roots, soak them in water,

282
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,710
mix them with hay,

283
00:18:36,710 --> 00:18:37,650
and dry them.

284
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,340
This way, it will be undetectable.

285
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,930
If they let the horses taste it,

286
00:18:42,070 --> 00:18:42,960
the horses

287
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,300
are much larger than goats.

288
00:18:44,710 --> 00:18:47,060
The effects won't show immediately.

289
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:51,170
As for how to get it to the enemy...

290
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:54,450
